// `det_send`'s ensures has the shape
//
//     (antecedent_conjunction) ==> det_send_equal(r1, r2, post1_self_, post2_self_)
//
// where the antecedent is the conjunction of `send`'s four ensures
// instantiated once for `(post1_self_, r1)` and once for `(post2_self_, r2)`,
// and the consequent reduces to
//
//     ((r1 is Ok) == (r2 is Ok))                         // discriminator agree
//     && (post1_self_.view() == post2_self_.view())      // NetClientView agree
//
// (the `r1 is Ok ==> r1->Ok_0 == r2->Ok_0` clause is trivially `() == ()`).
//
// The antecedent only constrains the three **closed `#[verifier::external_body]`**
// spec fns
//     NetClient::my_end_point()  -> AbstractEndPoint
//     NetClient::state()         -> State
//     NetClient::history()       -> History
// each of which Verus treats as a totally uninterpreted function (their bodies
// are `unimplemented!()`).
//
// The consequent's view-equality is on `NetClient::view()`, which the injected
// `impl View for NetClient { ... }` defines as
//
//     closed spec fn view(&self) -> NetClientView {
//         NetClientView { history: self.history@, end_point: self.end_point }
//     }
//
// — i.e. a *projection of the underlying NetClient struct fields*
// `self.history: Ghost<History>` (via `@`) and `self.end_point: EndPoint`.
//
// Crucially, there is **no source axiom — no open spec fn, no broadcast lemma,
// no `reveal_*`-able definition — that links the closed external_body spec fns
// `my_end_point()` / `state()` / `history()` to the struct fields
// `end_point` / `state@` / `history@`** that `view()` projects.  Two
// `NetClient` values can therefore agree on every closed-spec-fn output
// (satisfying the entire antecedent) while disagreeing on the struct fields
// (falsifying the consequent's `view()` equality).  The implication is
// genuinely not derivable from the supplied hypotheses, and any standalone
// assertion of an antecedent conjunct in the bare proof body (the prior
// attempt's mode of failure on
// `assert(post1_self_.my_end_point() == pre_self_.my_end_point());`) is
// unsound because those conjuncts are only available *under* the ensures'
// antecedent, not as facts in the proof body.
//
// We therefore restrict ourselves to sound let-bindings that anchor the
// closed-spec-fn outputs and the per-run `view()` / history-delta projections
// on common syntactic terms, so that any quantifier instantiation z3 attempts
// while discharging the implication-ensures is over a uniform e-graph.

let pre_endpoint:  AbstractEndPoint = pre_self_.my_end_point();
let p1_endpoint:   AbstractEndPoint = post1_self_.my_end_point();
let p2_endpoint:   AbstractEndPoint = post2_self_.my_end_point();

let pre_state_spec: State = pre_self_.state();
let p1_state_spec:  State = post1_self_.state();
let p2_state_spec:  State = post2_self_.state();

let pre_history_spec: History = pre_self_.history();
let p1_history_spec:  History = post1_self_.history();
let p2_history_spec:  History = post2_self_.history();

let p1_view: NetClientView = post1_self_.view();
let p2_view: NetClientView = post2_self_.view();

let history_delta1: Seq<NetEvent> =
    seq![LIoOp::Send { s: LPacket { dst: recipient@, src: p1_endpoint, msg: message@ } }];
let history_delta2: Seq<NetEvent> =
    seq![LIoOp::Send { s: LPacket { dst: recipient@, src: p2_endpoint, msg: message@ } }];
